Database Configuration
DATABASE_URL=postgres://postgres:test_123@localhost:5433/Chapter_One
DATABASE_POOL_MAX=20

Server Configuration
PORT=3001
NODE_ENV=development

Security
JWT_SECRET=change-this-to-a-secure-random-string-in-production
JWT_EXPIRY=24h
BCRYPT_ROUNDS=12

Electron Configuration
ELECTRON_IS_DEV=true

Customer pole display (USB serial, POS Sales — optional)
Set CUSTOMER_DISPLAY_PORT to your COM port (e.g. COM3 on Windows) to enable. Leave unset to disable.

Pure 8-digit 7-segment displays cannot show letters; use CUSTOMER_DISPLAY_MODE=numeric_only for amount-only, or use a two-line text/numeric pole for store name + price (default escpos_dual).

CUSTOMER_DISPLAY_ENABLED=1
CUSTOMER_DISPLAY_PORT=
CUSTOMER_DISPLAY_BAUD=9600
CUSTOMER_DISPLAY_MODE=escpos_dual
CUSTOMER_DISPLAY_NAME_MAX_CHARS=20